
<p>Thanks to kind effort of <a href="http://www.pastelero.net/">Angel
Abad</a> and <a href="http://sdziallas.blogspot.com/">Sebastian
Dziallas</a>, there are now official packages of current BlazeBlogger for
<a href="http://packages.debian.org/sid/blazeblogger">Debian</a> and
<a href="https://admin.fedoraproject.org/pkgdb/packages/name/blazeblogger">Fedora</a>
respectively. Arch Linux users can get both <a href="http://aur.archlinux.org/packages.php?ID=28974">stable</a>
and <a href="http://aur.archlinux.org/packages.php?ID=29153">development</a>
version from AUR.</p>

<p><strong>Update 2010/01/05:</strong> BlazeBlogger has recently made it to
<a href="http://packages.ubuntu.com/lucid/blazeblogger">Ubuntu Lucid Lynx</a>.</p>
